items.title: The 'middle powers' are having a moment, but can they stand up to Trump?
items.description: Some are looking to the world's "middle powers" as a possible bulwark against increasing unilateralism among global superpowers.

items.title: South Korea scrambles to pass U.S. investment bill after Trump threatens higher tariffs
items.description: The bill aims to establish a state-run investment corporation and fund to manage Seoul's planned $350 billion investment pledge to Washington.

items.title: ‘Never interrupt your adversary when he’s making a mistake’: Why Beijing isn't rushing to answer Trump’s tariff broadside
items.description: Analysts expect the U.S.-China trade truce to hold as Beijing bets Trump won’t follow through on his threats ahead of a leaders’ meeting in April.
